data.title: Victoria, Crown Princess of Sweden, Duchess of Vastergotland
data.text:
Victoria, Crown Princess of Sweden, Duchess of Västergötland (Victoria Ingrid Alice Désirée; born 14 July 1977), is the eldest child and heir apparent o King Carl XVI Gustaf. If she ascends to the throne as expected, she will be Sweden's fourth queen regnant (after Margaret, Christina and Ulrika Eleonora) and the first since 1720.

Marriage[edit]

On 19 June 2010, Crown Princess Victoria married a commoner Daniel Westling who had been acting as her personal trainer. After the marriage the couple moved to the Haga Palace. In the media the couple were called the "Crown Princess Couple"

Issue[edit]

Princess Estelle of Sweden, Duchess of Östergötland (born 23 February 2012)

Prince Oscar of Sweden, Duke of Skåne born 2 March 2016)

Titles and styles[edit]

14 July 1977 – 31 December 1979 Her Royal Highness Princess Victoria of Sweden.

1 January 1980 – 9 January 1980 Her Royal Highness The Crown Princess of Sweden.

9 January 1980 – present Her Royal Highness The Crown Princess of Sweden, The Duchess of Västergötland
